reviews: As a solo female traveller I found the location of this perfect, close to a metro, in a quiet area that felt safe. It was clean, stylish, easy to check into. I couldnt have really asked for any more considering the value.

Amazing staff great clean hotel, perfect location close to metro and bakeries. Rasheed and Angela were the most amazing staff! Kind and helpful best experience ive had with hotel staff! I will be back soon thankyou

LOCATION!!! this hotel is just steps away from the pipcus metro stop which made travelling around Paris (airport is easy aswell) a breeze although since it’s outside from city centre it is a bit of a travel BUT very easy to travel to and from! Area is well equipped with restaurants, shops etc to explore also very safe! This hotel/rooms is small but lovely (as you would expect for Paris) (the shower is super small but functional). No issues with check in (there is someone there 24hrs but if coming later /late at night best to notify a head of time as they’ll be sleeping/it’ll look like the hotel is closed). We were on the 7 floor with such an amazing view (still dream about it) * there’s is an elevator but only runs to the 6th floor then you have to take stairs. Overall great stay, definitely recommend and would stay here again :)

This boutique hotel is clean has lots of character , friendly and helpful staff. it is located close to Nation railway station with supermarkets, cafes,restuarants and a farmers market 2 days a week. the continental breakfast was one of the better ones I have experienced 9 euros a head. My only complaint was the flooring creaked ( real first world dramas) I can highly recommend it.

This is my third or fourth time staying at the Lux, and I like it and the neighborhood more each time I visit. I always get a superior double - worth the extra 10 euros for a bigger room, newer bathroom, tea kettle and fridg. I was bothered by the rumble of the subway in lower-floor rooms, but heard almost nothing this time in an upper floor room. The staff is excellent, and the breakfast at 9 euros is ample. Best of all is the convenience to many metro lines at Nation and several buses that go many places. You won’t find value like this (90 euros for a superior with breakfast) In many places. The neighborhood is very safe and very French.

A nice option for a 2 star hotel. Stayed at room 529 which was had a good size bath and bedroom compared to more expensive hotels. The room was warm with possibility to open the windows. But do bring earplugs cause you’ll hear the subway rumbling beneath you. The staff was friendly and spoke English.

Small 2 star hotel in the 12 arrondissement, a quite residential neighborhood. We were looking for a family room for a reasonable price and the Lux was spot on. The rooms are small but very clean and beds are comfy. The elevator is hardly large enough for 2-3 adults so with luggage it may be a challenge but it can be managed.
We had two stays in between trips to western France. We stayed once in the family suite which is 2 rooms next to each other and second time in the Family room which has 2 double beds. The family room option is a bit of a challenge in terms of space but not a deal breaker.
we had breakfast twice in the breakfast room at the cost of 9 euro PP. There are other options in the neighborhood which you may want to consider. Coffee and bread, and jam will run you between 3-5 euro at the cafe in the corner.
Keep in mind that you may be disturb from time to time by the rumble of the metro underground. For us it was not an issue.
in summary, there is nothing to fault for the price we pay we got an excellent return. We will definitely return on our next visit to Paris.

This hotel is close to a metro station and has lots of restaurants and shops nearby. Food market is excellent. Have stayed here over the years. Staff very friendly and helpful. Standard has been very consistent.

A friend recommended Lux Hotel Picpus to me and I'm so glad she did! Rachid and Corrine were wonderful hosts during my 12 night stay. The rooms are clean and neat and the hotel is intimate and homey. The Metro is steps out the door on a quiet street, the #29 Bus from Gare De Lyon drops you off a 1/2 block away, or the #351 Bus from the airport drops you off at Nation and it's about a 5+ minute walk to the hotel. Plenty of markets nearby. The room rate is fabulous and it's a very nice neighborhood! I'm a walker and in 45 min. I was in the main part of Paris! I would not hesitate to recommend this hotel to anyone and plan to stay at the Picpus when I return to Paris! Thank you Rachid and Corrine for your hospitality!

Second stay here. I like the superior standard rooms for just 10 euro or so more - bigger, newer baths and more comfortable than the older rooms The neighborhood is convenient to all sorts of public transports - Nation and Picpus metro stations and many buses.Lots of good neighborhood restaurants, bakeries, pharmacies, etc., and a great farmers' market twice a week. There are no big sites in this area, just real Parisian life in a safe, upper middle class neighborhood. Very reasonable rates. Very nice staff.

We have used this hotel on 4-5 occasions over 13 years. We found it by accident when searching for a reasonably priced hotel for a family holiday. It is 30 minutes by train from Disney, with the metro and train station called Nation just a very short walk from the hotel. This station takes you all over Paris and straight to Euro Disney.
The staff at Lux are pleasant and friendly. The buffet breakfast has a good and varied choice. The rooms clean, comfortable and good amenities are provided. Although the hotel doesn't serve evening meals there are lots of restaurants and eateries close by. Good value for money and we will always come back here when in Paris.

We spent three nights in Paris, and we were lucky to choose this hotel. It is very close to subway line 6. And nearby hotel, there is also carrefour supermarket and bio-market. The gentleman in front dest is very kind and nice to give us instruction. Although the space of room/shower is a bit smaller than we thought, but it is still a cozy hotel. We would be happy to recommend this hotel if you want a short visit to Paris.

Room & bathroom very small but comfortable. Nation & Picpus metro station nearby. Changed towels only one day. The little table fan was not sufficient for July heat. Wish there was AC. But overall our stay was very satisfying. Next time would definitely stay here.

The location is not bad just walking distance from Picpus metro station and close to Nation square-rooms are too small-I needed to take the elevator to get the 4th floor
and then walk some tiny dangerous stairs to get My room
The day I wanted to check out there was a French receptionist who were insisting that I had breakfast but did not pay !!!!!!!!!! His behavior made me upset

All the staff are very nice and friendly. The room is clean and comfortable. Location is good for me because you can take a bus just in front of the hotel, metro station on the left and RER on the right especially when you wanna to go Disneyland land. There are two markets nearby to the hotel so is convenient for us. Breakfast is simple and nice. It will be perfect for me If that is a air conditioner provided.

Stayed in this hotel during our family visit in Paris and found this hotel very good beds are comfortable,reasonable prices hotel,in the middle of market,bakery and grocery shops are near by, recommended for Indian families

I have been staying at this hotel for the past 12 years with nothing but good experiences. It is an older hotel but renovated. Clean fresh rooms , a bit small but very clean.
Service is second to none and they even had my room ready at 10:30 am when I arrived

A quiet area close to metro , restaurants and groceries and a bakery on the corner, 2 min away

I stayed here three times. I love this area , everything around, a lots of local restaurants, pharmacy, metro station. Room & toilet very clean. Staff friendly and helpful. I will come back here again in the next business trip.

The room isn't big but it has everything. Most important thing is its location. we took bus to there from the airport which is much more convenience than carrying the luggage up and down the stairs on the subway. ( most subway station doesn't have lift)

The LUX Picpus enjoys a nice location with metro connectivity.
This is away from the major tourist venues, but well connected via the Red line(Nation) and another metro directly connecting to Eiffel and Trocadero.
There is a bakery next door that is very nice.
Also, the hotel is clean and room is as in pics (But, a little small).
I had requested a room with bath and the request was accepted without any additional charges.
Overall it was a nice experience.

The staff speak english and are very helpful for directions and surrounding sights. Rooms were always clean and your own private bath. Breakfast is better than most others and includes eggs for soft boil or many other items. Just outside Paris and just steps from the metro.

This Hotel in the 12th arr. is such good value. I have now stayed there 6 times over the years and the quality and service stays consistent. Breakfast buffet is just what I need, staff friendly and efficient, also supplying me with ice for my nightcap, not all hotels are keen to do this, often pretending not to understand what you want. My room was in front to the street, but it is such a quiet neighbourhood, there is no noise at night and the view from the window is lovely, the boulevard in front has a very wide sidewalk and lots of big trees. The metro is just across the street and you can be at Arc de Triomph in no time, the line goes directly there. TV with many stations, everything you need at hand.

We stayed over a week. Nice little hotel, clean, has mini bar. It's a little out of the way. However, Picpus metro across from the hotel has good line 6 and several other lines in Nation metro, only 10 minutes walk.
Breakfast is EUR9 per person. A little pricey, I think. But if you don't like you could go elsewhere, but we ate at the hotel because it's convenience.
Wifi works in the lobby.

Excellent place for younger tourists. Fair prices; Rooms are rather small, so not adapted for tons of luggage; Very clean indeed (France had -once upon a time a bad reputation- but for some 20 years Hotel managements grew wiser and adapted themselves to very corect standards) Bathroom rather small but nice and nicely designed. We did not test their breakfast. Quiet at night, no roaring traffic; Metro around the corner + busses. Several good restaurants around the Place de la Nation. If you like fish, there is Le Dalou, Place de la Nation no. 30, Phone 0143434138. where you can dine or have supper until late at night.
Have fun, enjoy Paris ........

As a solo female traveler I stayed at this hotel for 4 nights in mid-December. The hotel is located in the 12th arrondissement in a relatively quiet area.There are plenty of restaurants nearby and two major metro lines within walking distance. When traveling to Paris I prefer to stay in locations that are not too central as costs are generally better and restaurants and other services nearby are not your typical tourist traps with inflated prices. The location was excellent though since I could reach central Paris in about 15 minutes via metro. My room was considered a 'superior' single, and was quite roomy even by Parisian standards. The room was equipped with the standard necessities and was quite comfortable and clean. My room faced onto the main street, and there was no problem with street noise. Although I do speak French, the staff also speak English quite well. The reception desk is manned 24/7 and I found the staff to be very helpful and pleasant-they really represent the hotel well. I decided to take the hotel's buffet breakfast each day, which included bread and pastries, cereals, charcuterie, cheese, eggs, juice and coffee. I found it to be a good value and a great convenience to have breakfast before I began my touristic visits each day. Without hesitation, I would stay at Lux Hotel Picpus on my next visit to Paris.

I think this is the cheapest clean decent paris hotel I can find and i am returning to lux hotel in april. It is a little far from the city central but not something a budget traveller cant deal with? The basic room is tiny. Please upgrade to a bigger room if need to. Not for choosy people pls. There is a french cake shop at the right of the hotel at attractive prices. Pls try. airport bus is also nearby.

Just a few steps from the metro and everything you need is just around the corner. Grocery stores wine shops and pastries are all close. I took a small room and had my own bath room. Breakfast is very nice including fresh bread, jams, and eggs. Every time I go to Paris I will stay here. Clean rooms and I just love it here.

My family and baby stayed at the Lux Hotel and we had a great time. It is located in a very quiet neighborhood full of local restaurants, pharmacies, a full service supermarket and even a small park for kids across the hotel. The metro station is convenient located. There's good WiFi reception in the lobby. McDonalds and Quick is not far either for those who would miss junk food after a while. You will simply not find a better deal in town for traveling on a budget.

Overall, very good hotel. The metro is very close to it, you can take it to go to the city center. Rooms are small but clean, and the location seems to be pretty safe. There are quite excellent shops nearby, like fast food, italian restaurants, laundry, boulangeries and even a BNP Paribas bank.
it's a small french hotel, but the room is very clean, the staff are all very friendly, the location is super, only 30 seconds from Picpus metro station, we enjoy our stay with the acceptable price.

My daughter and I recently stayed at the Lux Hotel Picpus. The hotel is very conveniently located across the street from the Metro (line 6). We easily used the Metro to reach all areas of Paris.

We loved the quiet (yet vibrant) residential neighborhood. It was always nice to return to the peaceful neighborhood after long days in the bustling, more congested areas of Paris. The neighborhood bakeries and restaurants were authentically French without feeling "touristy".

The hotel was warm and inviting, small but quite charming! The staff was friendly, efficient, and very helpful — they assisted us with printing museum tickets, boarding passes, dinner suggestions, etc... Our room was small, but we had a private bath — everything was spotlessly clean!

This cozy hotel will be our first choice when we return to Paris in the future!

We stayed in this hotel 3 nights at the beginning of November and it was a real pleasure. The location was close to many restaurants and shopping facilities. The metro station is nearby which is a great advantage if you want to visit Paris. We stayed in this hotel before and came back because we liked it. We would definitely stay in this hotel again next time we travel to Paris.

Relative large room with the similar rates you paid for the hotel in paris. 2 metro station nearby, picpus and nation. From picpus station station, you can directly arrive passy for Eiffel Tower night view!

Hotel is open 24 hours, which is good for traveller who arrive paris at night.

My room was located in 4th floor, but you can still hear the metro run by at night. It's not a problem for us since we always return hotel tiredly. But may not be quite fit in for light sleeper. One may look up in the web for how late does the metro stop service.

My stay was 9/12, I read positive reviews and decided to stay at Lux Hotel. The location is great, two metro stations are within walking distance. The staff was friendly and provided daily maid service. The price was terrific! My only "complaint" would be that there wasn't an English speaking tv channel. Granted I wasn't my room much and I didn't go to Paris to watch tv, but late at night and early in the morning, it would have been nice to watch a little news, even if the channel was CNN or BBC. (It could have been just my room possibly) Otherwise, this was a great hotel and I would definately stay here again!!

We chose the Lux Hotel Picpus for our accommodations for a brief 3 day stay in Paris. We were headed to Germany to board a cruise ship and decided to arrive in Europe (Paris) a few days early to adjust to the time difference. Our goal was a hotel that was good value, clean, and mostly had good connections to public transportation and trains to the airport. This hotel fit the bill. Located in a nice residential area near Nation Station it was very easy to reach by train from the CDG airport. We took the train with only one very easy change. We then walked the few blocks to the hotel.
The hotel itself met our needs perfectly. The room was quite small, but it was clean and quiet. The front desk was helpful. We suggest having the breakfast at the hotel unless you eat a light breakfast because there are no breakfast cafes in the area. You can always find a coffee and pastry, but if you want more, eat at the hotel.
Wifi was available to us and worked just fine.

Clean and comfortable room. Open buffet rich breakfast is 5 star! Location is good. 5min walking to Place Nation, full of nice restaurants. You can reach every attraction point with one direct metroline. Excellent value for the money paid. Don't miss!

I was back to this hotel last May 2014 with my friend and it was my 6th time staying at the hotel. We stayed for 4 nights and I still find it was excellent for B&B. The only disappointment was that I did not get my favorite room no 104. The staffs are the same person that I met the first time in 2001. The room and bath room is still clean and comfortable even it was so tiny. The way they served BF still the same the only the difference that they don't serve baguette fresh any more I was not happy. The service is still excellent and now they provide free wifi. It is a plus. I absolutely will come back when I visit Paris. Bravo

Spent one week here after reading many reviews of hotels in Paris. This is the best value I could find. Twin room, small bathroom, storage space for clothes, TV all in French, large window that opened, 5th floor rear, quiet, tiny elevator all for a good price in Paris dollars. Paris is very expensive. Ate breakfast at the hotel for an extra charge due to convenience. There are bakeries, a cleaning service, pharmacy, large and small groceries nearby. Ate a good priced meal (for Paris) at Marco Polo's up the street. Very near Picpus metro and 10 minutes from several metro lines at Nation station. Close to Pere Lachaise Cemetery and easy walk to historic Picpus Cemetery. Hotel is pretty far out, but in a nice neighborhood and easy metro/bus/RER transits to any tourist sites. Could store luggage after check-out. Hotel does not have AC, so might be pretty hot in mid summer. Met others there who were on a return stay due to the value and location. This is a good place for people on a budget.

Stayed here for three nights in a standard room. Room was small but very clean and towels replaced daily. Quiet neighborhood, but sometimes we could hear tram in the night. Metro stations Nation and Picpus are close to the hotel. Near the hotel, you have bakery and supermarket (fresh fruits).Staff was pleasant and helped us a lot with some advises.

I´ve been in this hotel many times before. When you are in the hotel, you have a clean, confort, and valuable place, far from crowds of tourists and noise. In this region (XIIeme arrondissemant) you find lots of good brasseries and restaurantes, and even a big departament store (Printemps, at Cours de Vincennes). The room is small (as in other hotels in Paris in the same category) but very clean. The bathroom is also small, and is the point that could be bettered, avoiding the plastic courtains. Very close to the Picpus metro station, and stiil close to Nation station, where you can catch a metro or RER to anywhere in the city with few or no connections. Breakfast generous, very recommended.

Stayed in one of the small rooms for 5 nights. Spotlessly clean hotel. Good transport links, with Metro line 6, "Picpus" and stops for bus routes 56 and 29 all being within 150 yards of the hotel.

Breakfast buffet is fine, although go early to avoid the scrum, as seating for barely 30, perhaps.

No air conditioning or international TV channels, but wi-fi in room is very good - for keeping up with events !

A good, budget hotel - but avoid in hot weather . . .

We stayed here several years ago and were very pleased with the hotel, its location, the breakfast buffet, and the service. It is near the Picpus and Nation metro stations which makes it a good place from which to see Paris. The price was very reasonable as I recall and the decor was tasteful and clean. I recall numerous restaurants conveniently located within a few blocks that were good. I will consider this nice little hotel again in the future.

Lux Hotel Picpus is situated at 5 minutes walking from Nation Metro Station which takes you to the city center in 10 minutes. I stayed in a superior double room with a bath tube. The room has been cleaned every morning and the furniture was modern. The bathroom is pretty big for a parisian hotel. I think that this buget hotel is perfect for a city break in Paris!

The hotel is very nice. Very clean, fair buffet for breakfast (for 8 EUR), friendly staff and extremely close to the metro station (Picpus).

It's true, it is away from the city centre and the touristic area (about 30 ~ 45 minutes away by metro). At the other hand, you can eat in restaurants and cafés with the locals, as it's not a tourists area (so, sometimes, the communication can be a little bit confuse). This neighborhood is quiet and safe at all.

The room as well as the bathroom are small, but don't expect anything much different in Paris. So, I would say that the size is good for Paris standards. The shower is OK. The sleep quality is average as depending on the hour you will be able to hear some noises from the metro or from the next room.

If you are looking for a nice and simple hotel and you find yourself in a budget and you don't care about the transit time of about half hour to the city main attractions, I would definitely recommend this hotel.

(stayed 5 days in July/2012)

I feel compelled to review this hotel as our recent experience was quite different than those older, very glowing ones online.
We stayed 7 days, we had 2 rooms at 62 euro each. Some days we took breakfast, this costs 8 euro per person. Breakfast consists of breads, yogurt, ham, cereals, cheeses, fruit, and a lovely big pot of fresh coffee. Its good value and was always served with a smile by the same friendly woman each day.
The room was pokey but clean and ours had great views over the street. Bed a bit saggy in the middle, linen all fine, towels changed daily, room cleaned nicely each day. Walls are thin, so anyone talking in the next room can be heard.
Location is good, shops nearby, including a small supermarket. Or you can walk to Nation and find a large supermarket. Across the road is the Metro stop Picpus. Exit the Metro and look straight across two small roads and you will see the hotel,, so very convenient. M6 Nation..light green line is the metro line to take. This line will also take you direct to Bir Hakeim stop for the effiel tower.

However...the hotel has some great aspects but it also has some serious shortcomings when it comes to the ability of the Reception staff. This man ruins what could be a fantastic hotel. A consistently sour attitude, half smile, turned up lip, arrogant strutting around the place, no eye contact, no hello, welcome, how are you, ever, to any in our party of 4. Even when we paid and checked out, no thank you and goodbye, just averted eyes and sudden busyness with nearest available distraction. I think he is an employee, but as the main person on reception, his attitude is an abomination. Definitely not the way to interact with guests.
In all the hundreds of hotels around the world we have stayed at from low to high budget, we have never encountered rude arrogance such as this.

Very clean, newly renovated, great buffet breakfast, friendly English speaking staff, close to the metro (only 1 min walk to Picpus station) = Value for money - simply more than a 2 star hotel! One pity is that it is a bit away from the center (about 30-45mins away in total by metro to the main attractions and tourist area in general), but being close to Picpus and Nation stations makes it easy to get there. The area is quiet and safe. I loved the breakfast, including fresh bread and great croissants everyday :) The young receptionist, who was there in the weekend, was very efficient and friendly. He also arranged for us a shuttle van for our way back to the hotel (ask for it upon arrival to see availability and pre-book it - it was very efficient and cheaper than a taxi). The ladies at the breakfast were very nice and friendly too. The only small other pity was that you don't have any tea/coffee making facilities in the room, which in Winter would have helped after a day out, but all the rest was great, so I would definitely recommend this hotel! Thanks :)

Clean, newly renovated, friendly English speaking staff, close to the metro---amazing hotel!!!

We were very happy with this hotel and the best part is that the metro station closest (pic pus) has all of the major spots on that line (green-6)

We opted for the least expensive room - 62 euros a night. We stayed here at the beginning and end of our trip so we had two different rooms. We found the location quiet and convenient. Major city attractions are only a short metro ride away. Staff was very professional and the rooms were very clean. The rooms were small but adequate.

I stayed in Lux Hotel for 4 nights, the staff was friendly and English was spoken without any problems. Room was small or big enough but clean and quiet on the 4th floor looking out on the street. During the day you could barely hear the rumble of the metro but they stop running after 00.30 anyway. It is a bit away from the center and tourist area in general but being close to Nation it is not even worth mentioning it and also it is in a quiet and safe neighborhood, I walked from Bercy to the hotel one night from the concert after midnight and I never for the moment felt threatened in any way. I totally recommend this little place and if I go back to Paris I will surely look for available rooms there first.

My wife and I had stayed at this property a few times some years ago, but this is the first time we have stayed here in the last 5 years. The room rate was cheap (just 70 per night) and we opted for a Superior Room. Our room was on the first floor and, on a Summer's evening, it was extremely pleasant to leave the windows open, hear the noise of the street and watch the leaves of the trees lit up by spotlights.
The hotel is right beside a Metro station (Picpus) but we also found that we could walk into the centre of Paris in less than an hour.
A breakfast is served each morning (for a few euro extra).
The room was small enough (as Paris hotel rooms tend to be) but clean.
Highly recommended for those who want to experience Paris but don't want to pay inflated city centre prices.

Now I know why this hotel is so highly rated among the travellers. It really deserve the rating and my praise for their cleanliness. The hotel room is very clean, especially the toilet, I can almost see the spark shine from the toilet bowl.

I think this hotel had just newly renovated, because it look almost new everything to me.The room size is moderate to me standard but in paris consider it good enough.

This hotel does got a small elavator, but is a working one !

Nearby this hotel there is tons of cafe and restaurant. There is few bakery, some grocery, a supermarket, few laundrette, few phamarcy and all other possible service you needed within 5 minute of walking. Its far too convenient for tourist, is more like a place I would choose to stay for long time :D

The Picpus metro is just across the hotel, Line 1 and RER Nation is just 5 minute walk away. Superb transportation! Going to airport , i use the hotel shuttle, only EURO 18 per person, took about 50 minutes in early morning traffic. Very good service!

However, this hotel room just like most euro hotel , is not air condition, so i do not in summer how warm it can get, but in this cool weather, the room is just fine. and during my 3 night stay , the last night get little cold, I turn on the bath room heater, the whole room is warm up to a very comfortable temperature.

I greatly recommend this hotel to anyone and every one ! For the price I pay, is not just a gem but a diamond class value !

located in a quiet area with good restaurants, pasterries and supermarkets around the corner. walking distance to both nation and picpus metro station. room size is moderate but the lift size is a little small, only can fit 3 passengers at one time. a few minor flaws, you can feel the vibration everytime the metro passes and toilet window is just covered with a sheer curtain.

I stayed at this hotel based in the good reviews and the reviews were right. Excellent hotel with a very friendly and helpful staff. This was my first trip to Paris and it was lovely. The hotel is located in the 12 arrodisiemt and well away from the tourist part of Paris. I and my husband do not speak French and had I known that in this area hardly nobody speaks English I would not have stayed here but because the hotel was excellent and the people around this neighborhood were so friendly and helpful I would deffinwtly stay here again. The room I stayed in was very clean and modern and the metro is located a few steps away and was very convenient. I was really sick with a cold one day an lost a day in Paris :( The gentlemen at the front desk that evening was nice enough to help us order out and to let my husband know that the medicine he bought from the pharmacy that is less then a minute walk would help my condition. Overall good experience. :)

this was my 4th visit in paris and this is probably the best hotel i stayed in, the best value. the hotel is situated on blv. de picpus just 50m from the picpus metro station and 200 from nation metro station which is on the line 1, you will probably use it more often to get to most of paris attractions. if you fly with a low cost on beauvais airport the metro from port maillot takes you straight to nation.

you can get also get the metro from picpus to nation if you don't want walk the distance although is not much and this is zone of paris is very safe, i walked this streets also in the night and it was ok. so if you return from the city during night it's ok to walk from place de la nation to the hotel.

from picpus station you can easily go on the left bank of sena, to place d'italie where you can change for line 7 for rue mouffetard - pantheon etc. also just in front of the hotel is a bus station, bus no 56 which takes you to place de la republique.

so as you can see the hotel is well bounded with the city but if this is your first time in paris i think you should look for a hotel situated more in the centre of paris, if you are not familiarized with the transport in paris and if you dont want to lose a lot of time in the metro.

about the room, i had a single room, small but ok with a bathroom that was also tiny. very clean with a very comfortable and big enough bed. there is no AC in the room, at least not in my room, but i didn't see any AC device on the building, the wi-fi signal was fair i didn't use it much. there is also a tv but with only 15 programs all in french. the hotel has a small elevator that goes up to the 6th floor, the hotel has 7 floors so for the last one you have to walk the stairs. the very very big minus is that you can hear absolutely everything is going on in the rooms next to you. unfortunately on 2 nights my neighbours from one room were very blatant until almost 1 AM. so take some earplugs, even if you are not used with them take a pair.

if you want you can serve breakfast for 8 euro, i didn't because on the way to place de la nation there is a nice boulangerie (picpus bakery) and you can buy from there something for the morning.

i didn't interact much with the staff only when i left and took the card for the door, i once asked something about the metro and the man from the desk didn't seem to have any ideea, whatever.

prices for the rooms from what i've seen are very good, you pay the same but for low quality in most of other paris hotels, so for a 2 star this is good option.

Since 2003, I have stayed 5 times in the Lux Hotel Picpus, Paris, once for more than a week. I find everything about the hotel and location very convenient. The area around the hotel is like a village, with everything from restaurants, grocery stores, bakery, fishmonger, butchery and even a laundry close by. I loved watching a group of men paying boules in a small park. Metro statuin Picpus is just across 2 roads and the big Nation station is also very close. I love going to the Père Lachaise cemetery, and I usually walk there, about 20 minutes , a very pleasant walk on a Sunday morning.
Also the breakfast is very good for the €8 that is charged. The vicinity is also quiet with no late night noisy traffic.

5 metro stops from down town Paris.and about a 5 minute walk to Metro. No AC so for those that travel in the summer heat be prepared to sleep with your window wide open.(fan provided) So pick a room on the inside away from traffic and direct sun hitting room all day.Price reasonable and breakfast very good. Grocery up the block 5 minutes away also.

Great for travellers on a budget and in a French residential area away from the main tourist areas. The rooms and bathrooms are very small. The rooms were very stuffy in the summer heat and we had to remove a plastic mattress protector to get any comfort.

Staying in Paris can be very expensive. Lux Hotel Picpus is a small but cosy establishment that would please shoestring budget travelers. The prices of a standard room here are comparable to what you would expect to pay for a private room in a hostel in a touristy part of the city.

I stayed at Lux for 4 nights in June. Although it was not walking distance from the most visited Parisian attractions, e.g. Eiffel, Louvre etc, it was a convenient metro ride from them. It was 1 RER stop from Gare de Lyon, 2 stops from Chatelet Les Halles (near the Louvre) and 4 stops from Charles de Gaulle Etoile (where Arc de Triomphe is). Since all these RER stations are within Zone 1, a regular metro ticket will do just fine. I found only a few places, such as Montmartre, to be a tad further away but still within 30 minutes of travel.

The hotel was a 5-minute walk from the Nation metro station. Situated in a lovely Parisian residential neighborhood in the 12th arrondissement, it was away from the madness and bustle of the touristy areas and exuded an endearing Parisian charm. The sidewalk along the main road comes alive on weekends with locals armed with shopping trolleys heading to the open-air market (the Marché Cours de Vincennes, if I am not wrong). With the colorful array of fresh produce and tasty hot food, it's impossible to miss.

The room I stayed in was simple and cosy, and most importantly spotlessly clean. There was the usual you'd expect in a regular hotel- dressing table, TV, wardrobe, comfy bed, space to place your luggage, clean en-suite toilet with toiletries and reliable hot shower, fresh towels and daily room service. The reception was polite and helpful, and the daily breakfast buffet was simple but value for money. Sure, the room wasn't sprawlingly spacious, but it was decent, comfortable and provided great value for money.

I'd stay here in a heartbeat again the next time I'm in Paris.

I had been to this hotel in 2006 and came back in June this year. It's good to see that the hotel remains good value for money with well appointed rooms (it's still Paris, so a bit on the small side). What I like most about this hotel is the location (12eme arrondisement) because it's a true Parsiian neighborhood with excellent transportation in the very close Nation (RER, metro, buses, taxis, bus to CDG airport), decent variety of restaurants, excellent bakeries, supermarket, etc. Their breakfast is also good value with full hot buffet for 8 euros. The Spanish speaking woman at breakfast is the nicest staff in the hotel, the reception staff can be nicer, but are still always useful and efficient. If you are in this hotel on a Saturday, I would highly recomment the market on the main road (Vincennnes), a true parisian experience.

We visited Paris in June 2013 and choose Lux hotel based on reviews on TA,must say we were not disappointed. The hotel is located in a quite a neighborhood and very close to Picpus metro (2 mins walk) and Nation station (5 mins walk). It takes about 30 mins to reach the major tourist spots by metro/train. There are supermarkets and shops near Nation station. The hotel staff are very good and helpful. The room was clean and had a small TV, table, safe for valuables and a wardrobe to hang clothes. There was a slight rumbling from the metro even on the 5th floor but it wasn't loud enough to disturb our sleep. The bathroom was quite cramped but extremely clean and well maintained throughout our stay. shower gel,soap etc were provided as well. The room & bathroom were cleaned very well on all days that we stayed there. The buffet breakfast is very good value for money. They have lots of options to choose from and it was very fresh as well. We had a very memorable stay at Lux hotel.

Pretty tiny hotel on the suburbs of Paris, but is not that bad, they have a pretty near metro station and you can easy get to the center of the city. The hotel were average, its like a polly pocket hotel everything were tiny, if you travel with a lot of luggage it can get uncomfortable. The price is ok so you get for what you pay for, the rooms are nice and clean.

I stayed here for a total of five nights, and, since I was traveling with a grad student, wanted to find a place we both could afford. This fit the bill. It's hard to get a decent room in a good neighborhood in Paris for less than USD 100, and this fit the bill nicely. The rooms are, by North American standards, awfully small, as many others have noted. Also, they are not air conditioned, but June in Paris is not so hot usually. There is street noise if you leave the windows open, but it's a good neighborhood. This hotel is far from central Paris, but the Picpus metro on the 6 line is less than 100 meters from the front door, and the neighborhood, in the 12th arrondissement, is quite charming. It's not at all touristy/chic (it's not the 7th!) but it has this great neighborhood vibe, with at least two decent cafes, an outstanding bakery, a very friendly dry cleaner next door, and the BNP Parisbas ATM right across the street. Indeed, everyone was extremely friendly, even when my college-level French failed me.

My room was spotless, and the hotel was always clean and kept up. The elevator/lift is very small, enough for one person and their bags. Be prepared! The shower in my room was tiny, but I'm a big guy.

My only very minor complaints were that it was very hard to get an outside phone line to use my Orange telephone ticket; the WiFi was extremely slow at times; and breakfast, as others have noted, is EUR 8.00. The breakfast room is small but nice, and it's convenient.

I plan to stay here again. It's lovely.

We have stayed at this hotel 4 different times now and it has been great. Twice last summer, and twice this summer. Cheapest room is a "Standard" for 60 Euros with a private shower (make sure to clarify). It is perfect for two young people on a budget and very clean! It is near about 4 boulangeries, an alimentation on the corner on the way to the Metro with fresh fruits/veggies, a post office on the street behind it. Staff is nice, you can get in 24 hours with a simple ring of the doorbell. It's about a 5-10 walk to the Metro, 5 if you walk faster. The rooms are a bit noisy in the morning and you can hear the Metro rumble underneath the building every 5 minutes, but I sleep with earplugs like a rock personally. The street itself it very quiet at night, being more residential/daytime shops.
Warning: The Metro in Paris stops running at 1 a.m. Not sure if this is the same weekdays and weekends. We learned this the hard way. Then you cannot get a bus. One stopped but it was jammed full, I mean jammed. And no taxi will stop. We had to walk... and got to the hotel about 3 a.m. that night :) But we got some great night pics on the Eifel Tower!!!

In a city like Paris, where hotel rooms are small and expensive, Lux hotel Picpus is a pretty good deal. Although not located in Paris center, it is at a stone's throw distance from Picpus Metro and 10 min walk to Nation station. Rooms are spacious enough and comfortable - we took the family suite which is basically two double bedrooms and a common hallway - pretty decent. The 8 euro pp buffet breakfast is satisfactory. Don't miss the pizzeria Nonna Rita nearby - great pizzas and pana cotta. Cafe Cosy serves great creme brulee.

We stayed at the Lux during our 1st trip to Paris.It was perfect for us.Room was small,yet it had been updated and they made great use of all space.Room was clean,beds comfortable.Bathroom was great.Good size,plenty of counterspace,nice shower with good water pressure and lots of hot water.On site private parking,quiet neighborhood with laundry 2 doors down-delivered to the hotel.Main metro station- 5 minute walk,smaller station right around the corner.The breakfast was extra,but cheap-about 12 euros per day for 2 people.Hotel staff was great,they helped us arrange a dinner cruise,directed us to the Metro and which line we should take to see all the sites.The Lux was very affordable and comfortable.We liked that it was off the main drag,yet numerous restaurants within walking distance.25-30 minute metro ride to all the main sites.Saturday morning there was a huge farmers market on a nearby street-highly recommend this hotel.

We found this hotel perfect for our needs. Its plain, not fancy at all and a bit away from most tourist attractions, but the Metro is close and we enjoyed the quiet neighborhood. Staff were helpful if not overly friendly. The breakfast was good and a relative bargain for Paris. For the price (we paid 70 euro) this was a great deal.

Be careful when booking hotels in Paris as there are some dodgey areas, not here, we stayed here for three nights. We had the family room. Nice and clean. Not luxurious but very good value considering how expensive Paris is. You can use the Metro (Picpus) to get around which is a very short walk or you could walk to Nation which has excellent links into central Paris. I would definitely stay here again. A good find thanks to Trip Advisor.

Lux Hotel Picpus is a very good option for the budget-conscious traveler. What sets the place apart from many inexpensive hotels is that the staff works quite hard to keep the hotel going along. Linens and furnishings in the rooms, while basic, are in good condition; the housekeepers keep the rooms nice and clean, and the front desk staff are energetic and helpful.

The location is not especially convenient, but that has the advantage of keeping you out and about (as you should be) rather than returning to the hotel for naps (which you can take when you get back home). Nation metro station isn't bad though, since it has both the 1 line and the RER. Also you can walk from the Lux Hotel Picpus to the Promenade Plantee which is a lovely and unusual garden built on a series of bridges and small streets and that merits a visit.

As other reviewers have commented, the 8-Euro breakfast is not good value... but hotel breakfasts are notoriously overpriced so this complaint could be made about almost any hotel. If you want something that tastes better you can go around the corner to "Le Triomphe" on the rue du Rendez-Vous and sample their fine pastries and prepared foods, but this might cost more than 8 Euros.

One thing that Lux Hotel Picpus could do to improve is to not charge guests 30 cents per minute for local telephone calls. This phone charge is abusively high and should be sharply reduced or eliminated. Many travelers will use their own phones anyway, and people traveling without personal cell phones should not be taken advantage of in this old-fashioned, penny-pinching way.

Perfect location. 2 minute walk from Picpus station and 7 minute walk to Nation station.
Helpful staff. They helped me to check in early. Gives you warm welcome and gives good advice especially on cheap transport option to the airport.
Basic Hotel. I booked a Deluxe room.
Good Breakfast! get me going until 3PM:)

I have stayed here 4 times (2000, 2007, 2010, 2013) as a single tourist. This is a small (39 room) hotel in the 11th arrondisement near Place de la Nation. I have always had a 'standard' room - small but clean and comfortable - with a double bed, small desk and chair, wardrobe, 13" TV (only French channels), and small bathroom. The standard room (60 euros) works well as a single, but couples should get a superior (70 euros) room. Breakfast (8 euros) is nice with croissants, baguettes, cold cuts, fruit, yogurt, cereal, coffee and juice. The hotel is on a quiet, safe street just south of Place de la Nation, which is a major public transport hub. While the Picpus metro stop is right nearby, you should walk 5 minutes to the Nation station - the RER A and Metro 1 lines run right down the Right Bank and connect with the RER B line to both CDG and Orly airports. The staff is helpful, and there is 24 hr front desk staffing. You can hear some subway noise if you stay on the first floor, but it is not bothersome. The furniture is a bit dated and worn (it hasn't changed since my first stay in 2000) - but it is still my 'home away from home' when I visit Paris. You will not find a better value in Paris.

We stayed 2 nights in a second floor room. The room was OK - not too small and the bed comfortable. The shower was a problem - water swilled over the shower tray and wet the floor up to the laminate flooring. Reception was good - staff were very helpful; breakfast was plentiful and again staff very helpful. The WiFi worked superb. We also used the garage behind for parking which was not cheap but convenient. (When we first arrived we had to jostle to get a space outside to off load. The best thing about the hotel was the 2 minute work to the metro line with quick transport into the centre and everywhere. So good value I guess in this very expensive city

Stayed for four nights, the rooms is spacious and very clean, all you need for a few nights, downside is we stayed when a group of italians and the first day we could here every door and step they made, very thin walls but it was only that day we got awaked by our neighbours, not big deal, the receptionists are nice specially the one at night and the location is next to a subway station, I do recomend it for the price. Just a tip, do not tell them to book you a taxi to the airport, it costs us 75 Euros, which we thought it was way too much but at the en dof the day, our mistake for not asking before or had looked an alternative to get to the airport.
All in all great city and good hotel.

We had a triple on floor 5, it was quite small but big enough for us. The bathroom was the second smallest I've ever had in a hotel, but at least the shower had a curtain and the shower pan had a lip (no awkward shower-over-the-toilet arrangements). Everything was very clean. The beds were very comfortable. We didn't try the breakfast, as there are nice bakeries and bars (for coffee) on nearby Rue du Rendez-Vous. We did hear the rumble of the trains (which end at around 1AM), also the neighbors arguing (they probably heard us better). The staff is friendly and helpful. The wifi was unpredictable: sometimes it was like dialup, sometimes we had 3Mb/s or more. The neighborhood is safe but not exactly charming, and quite far from tourist centers, but 1.2 euros will get you anywhere in Paris (if you buy metro tickets in carnets) so who cares?

One warning: if you leave your luggage after check-out for later retrieval, it will just be kept in the lobby, not behind closed doors. This made us a little nervous, though it worked out OK for us.

This small hotel in a quiet neighborhood in Paris was a very good value for the money. The hotel was clean, the staff was friendly, and it was located near two Metro lines so you can go anywhere in Paris you wish to go. The breakfast of 8 euros was worth the price.

Great value for money hotel. The rooms are clean and comfortable and the staff was helpful and friendly.It is located a couple of minutes away from the metro. There are a few places to eat around and the streets are safe for walking around during the night.

Only a 5 minute walk to Nation metro (with lines to everywhere, unlike Picpus) and boulangeries, supermarkets and cafes nearby, this hotel is in a good location. Sure, it is not amongst the action, but those places are twice the price. Safe neighbourhood too.

Rooms are small, typical Paris, we were three in a triple for 6 nights, so close quarters, but it was fine. Very clean, fresh towels daily if needed. There's an old fashioned heater and extra blankets, so cosy and warm. A fridge also, with mini bar soft drinks.

The buffet breakfast for €8 each was great. Cereal, fruit, yoghurt, boiled egg, toast, bread, cheese, croissant and tea kept us going till 3pm!

Highly recommended.

Comfortable, clean, small rooms. The desk clerks were kind and helpful. The hotel was located in a nice area with bakeries, fruit stands and a nice grocerie market nearby. The hotel was a five minute walk from a large metro station. I would definetly stay there again ;}

Fantastic value for Paris and only a short metro trip from the main attractions. I requested a room on a higher floor after reading other reviews and comments on noise from metro. We were on the 6th floor and had no sleeping problems

October, 2012: I had booked two other hotels but cancelled them after reading reviews, and then found Lux Hotel Picpus which had only positive comments and was just a few Euros more. It did not disappoint! The hotel is very conveniently located across from a Metro stop, has a lovely street of shops and cafes around the corner and is meticulously clean with a good shower and terrific mattress. Perfect situation. It has my enthusiastic recommendation!

We were very impressed with this hotel. It is very near nation metro which meant most of the main sites were about 20 minds away by metro. The booking was easy and the hotel communicated swiftly via email. When we arrived we were given room 209. The room was a reasonable size with a good sized bathroom. I've stayed in other Paris hotels and this was easily the biggest and best bathroom...bath, strong pressure shooter and plenty of hot water. The room and hotel was spotless. The staff were pleasant and not overly familiar which I consider a good attribute. The breakfast was great...tea, coffee, pastries, yoghurt, cheese, meat, eggs etc. a great choice and the lady who ran the room was lovely and tolerated my poor French.
some reviews mention noise...our room faced a shaft which wasn't pretty but meant that street noise was minimal. You could feel rather than hear the metro but it didn't bother us...I slept very well and the bed was very good. We unfortunately had some very rude neighbours who felt it appropriate to talk and laugh very loudly at half past eleven at night but that isn't the hotels problem add much as a lack of manners from guests.
The area was nice and safe feeling although there is a poor homeless man who was living in the phone box outside the door...he was there everytime we came and went for a week but he didn't seem dangerous.
Overall this hotel was great value for money and we'd stay there again.

I read other positive reviews on this hotel and decided to try it. I arrived early and was pleasantly surprised that my room was ready. I was greeted very warmly and efficiently, the process was so quick!
My room was on the first floor, very nicely sized for one person. The bed was very comfortable and clean. The bathroom was small, but the shower was powerful and the water nice and hot! I had read reviews that commented on metro noise, but I was not in my room enough to notice it, nor did it keep me awake. Being close to 2 metro stops was so convienent! I had such an enjoyable stay here at the Lux Hotel Picpus, and I would definately stay there again my next trip to Paris!!

Seriously great value in Paris.

Well fitted and modern (very nice bathrooms) though admittedly small rooms. Central enough location to make walking into the centre very doable.

Definitely a good choice!

Friendly staff, not overly informative but will try to help you.

Room itself for €70 (breakfast an extra €6) had heater, phone, tv, desk, wardrobe, double bed, mini fridge and a great private ensuite.

Nothing special to look at but very clean and comfortable. And the bath was just a bonus.

Very close to lots of resaurants, shopping spots and supermarkets, including a small one open till midnight.

This is our 2nd time staying @ The Lux Hotel Picpus....We enjoyed it.....Paris being expensive this is a good budget hotel....The rooms are small but if your out sight seeing all day and just enough time to sleep in the hotel, its all good.....The bathroom was tiny as well BUT it was remolded so it made up for it...We stayed on the 4th floor so we didn't hear the metro but it could have been we were sooo exhausted we fell asleep pretty hard....The staff are nice & helpful, always had a smile and willing to answer any questions you had....If your looking for a high quality hotel, this hotel is not the hotel your looking for....This is a practical, working class persons hotel for people on a budget visiting Paris.....

The location is very good tow minutes walk from the metro and the rer station. There are a bunch of supermarkets and bakeries around the hotel. The staff were very nice. However, the rooms were small but very clean and we heard noises from the room near by all the time.

This hotel is only a few euros more than you would pay for an en-suited room at hotels like Appi and Liberty, but far superior in facilities and comfort - the difference being that it is quite far from the sites. We found we had to use the Metro every day of the six days we stayed there, whereas we didn't use it at all when we stayed in the other two hotels. It's well worth it for the extra comfort, and Picpus Metro is just across the road.

There is one drawback, which can be a serious one for some people. On our first night, my wife could not sleep because she was badly affected by the rumble of the Metro trains. We thought we would have to change hotels, but the next day we were given another room, two floors higher and at the front of the hotel, and it was no longer a problem. We could still hear the trains, but it was more distant and probably drowned out by the general street noise, which didn't bother us. So Room 209 was no good for us, whereas 428 was perfectly all right. The bathroom in the second room was much smaller, but adequate and clean. It was great to have a fridge, which enabled us to eat some meals in the room, though it was a bit strange having the safety deposit box pretty much inside the fridge! TV worked well, as did the WiFi.

As is usually the case in French hotels, there were no tea and coffee making facilities in the room. However, the hotel was very obliging in providing us with a jug of hot water when we wanted to make our own drinks - not always quite hot enough, but it was very welcome. The staff were friendly and helpful, and spoke English. They were happy to print out some e-tickets for us and were reliable in giving us a wake-up call on our last morning.

There are reasonable restaurants in the area, an excellent boulanger on the corner, and the usual charcuteries, fromageries, supermarkets, etc. nearby. There is also a great market on Saturday morning along Cours de Vincennes.

We enjoyed our stay at Lux Hotel very much and will certainly return next time we go to Paris.

I stayed here 3N during end of May 2012 with my wife. I would say its a pretty decent hotel and very conveniently located near 2 metro stations. you can reach to any tourist destination in Paris within 30-35mins using metro. Picpus is the nearest, although sometimes you hear the train rumbling beneath you but its won't disturb you. Breakfast is pretty good with lot of options like cereals, breads, cakes, fresh and cut fruits, milk, coffee, tea ... (and all for €8). There is also a minibar in the room and a safe. There is no fan or A/C, but even though it was a hot weekend, it was not a issue, you might open the windows(it might feel unsafe but it's fine)There are some pretty good restaurants nearby(Italian, Vietnamese and many French cafes). I felt its pretty safe to be around in night. And the staff and well mannered and welcoming. All in all I would recommend this and if I will be definitely staying here if I go to Paris again.

we stayed for three nights,very near picpus metro and Nation(RER). Quite neighborhood. Even the noise from underground metro did not disturb us. We went to this hotel based on previous reviews and we were not disappointed.The Staff was very helpful and courteous.

Considering you´re not in a very special neighbourhood (not very close to the main Paris attractions), you have a clean hotel, with adequate accomodations, great breakfast, gentle workers, close to restaurants and brasseries were Parisian use to eat. Very close to Picpus (just in front) and Nation stations of metro. Cheaper and better than the majority of the hotels in its category. I´ve been there six times, never disappointed. Well, if you have very sensitive ears, you can hear the metro...

My single room was very clean and the matrress was soft. The room was tiny and the furniture older but the bathroom was renovated. For EUR 70 you can not complain. The breakfast had a good choice and all the staff are friendly and helpful. The hotel is very close to the metro station and around the hotel are restaurants, bakeries and a food shop, where you can buy soft drinks etc. I believe for a single traveller the rate is very good value. I felt very save when I got home late in the night. The only negative point is the metro, which you can hear from the rooms in the lower part of the building.

My teen-aged daughter and I stayed at the Lux Hotel Picpus in early June. We loved it!! We loved "our little neighborhood". After sight seeing all day and coming back bone weary it was such a relief to come back to clean and comfortable beds. The bathroom and shower were great. We could hear the street noise but it didn't bother us at all. We did not have breakfast at the hotel instead we bought delicious pastries just a few doors down and had great coffee at the Cafe Cozy just down the street. The staff was polite and helpful. The metro is just a few steps away and will get you to all the sights in no time. I would stay here again and would recommend it to anyone wanting a clean, safe room for a bargain.

!!!!!!The reviews were very helpful and true to form. This hotel was everything I expected. There is a higher level of sound from the city but it is part of being in a city. The room was an excellent value and very clean, well kept and pleasent. We couldn't have asked for more.

My wife & I stayed at the Hotel Lux Picpus for 3 nights in early June 2012.

We selected this hotel based on tripadvisor reviews.

We knew beforehand that this hotel is a little distant from the centre of Paris and we preferred this however,all the main tourist sights are within easy reach by the metro station called Nation 500 metres or Picpus 100 metres.

There are many places to eat or buy food all within easy walking distance to the hotel. These are good after a days sightseeing in the city. We found these reasonably priced for Paris away from the tourist areas.

We stayed in a double room which was clean,spacious with good shower, toilet facilities & TV.
The room is very elegantly decorated.

We had a good view looking out into the main street but did not find this noisy when the windows were closed. There is sometimes a humming noise apparent from the trains on the metro but very minimal and this was no inconvenience to us.

The buffet breakfast is very good with a selection of breads,hams and cheese all very fresh plus the usual jams, coffee and teas.

The owners obviously pride themselves on the cleanliness of the hotel and the facilities they provide. We found them to be very quiet yet helpful when needed.

We enjoyed our stay and would highly recommend this hotel. We would have no hesitation in booking here again should we visit Paris.

If travelling to the airport after your stay there is a bus near the Nation station which will take you direct and cheaply. The owners will give you the information.

A bit of noise issues with the Metro train running under the hotel and the street noise but this is Paris and one often has to choose between closing the window at night in the summer to damper the street noise yet suffer in a hot/warm room or leave the window open and enjoy the night air with the noise it comes with. I chose to close my window but the room was quite warm at night with this choice. Funny story... I was outside just before 5 a.m. one morning and talking with someone on the street. A guest poked her head outside her open window and asked if we could carry on our conversation at some other location. Ummm... okay. Nice breakfast, very hospitable, personable staff and good rates. Small rooms with even smaller bathroom and shower but I would stay here again for the good rate and fine staff.

Urm... where to start?! Well for 40 euros each a night during the summer months, I must confess that I was pleasantly surprised by the cleanliness of the bedroom and bathroom. Shower was powerful (although without a holder...grrrr!... pet hate of mine! How do you wash your hair?!?) and bed was relatively comfortable. The staff were friendly enough too (didn't exactly go out of their way to tell us anything at all about Paris/provide a map etc but as we had been there a few times it was ok for us). Location was pleasant too... little bit of surburbia in Paris but close to everything too (i.e. bastille, Notre-Dame etc)

The hotel was so noisy though!! Walls were paper thin so you could hear people talking and tvs etc and also there was some kind of car park next door and the extremely squeaky gate (which operated a flashing orange light every time it opened) was opening and closing all night.

If you are after a cheap and cheerful experience quite close to the centre of Paris I would recommend, but if you are after a romantic, luxury weekend away with your partner I would advise against!

We were looking for budget but safe accommodation and in all fairness, this is what this hotel delivers. We had come to visit Paris, not to hang around a hotel during the daytime.

The location is not bad - there is a metro station (Picpus) just across the road and a quite substantial metro / RER station at Nation just a 10 minute walk away.

The bedroom was absolutely spotless and came with a fridge which was useful. I know we were looking for budget accommodation but even so the room was quite a squeeze - there was really not enough space for both of us to be moving around the room at the same time.

The receptionists were always friendly and attentive and open 24 hours a day.

The main problem is that we were kept awake by the rumbling of trains going into the station every 5 minutes, the only respite being from 1 am to 5 am. Unlike other contributors, we could not "get used to it" and it spoiled our sleep.

Don't bother with the Euro 8 charge for breakfast - there are plenty of nearby patisseries where you can enjoy lovely pies, tarts with a cup of coffee.

If you are staying over a Saturday, be sure to go to the market which is held along the Cours de Vincennes behind the hotel.

After reading the reviews here we booked in for a week and have just returned. The staff were great, the inclusive breakfast was actually pretty good - help yourself, and not just 1 croissant and some jam dumped on a plate! and they serve it until 10:00 am - very civilised. The room passed the "is it clean test" from the wife - and this doesn't happen very often. The room was "bijou" to use a french phrase, but as we only slept in it, it didn't really matter, especially for the price that we were paying (excellent for Paris). I would have liked a little more sound insulation from our neighbours, but apart from that we'll be using it again when we return.
Just a little request - maybe some tea and coffee facilities in the room - would be appreciated.
Location was excellent for the Metro with a station across the road and a larger Metro at the next stop for transfers.

Nice experience during my stay in Lux Hotel in Paris. Clean and complete with the ammenities.
The room was small for a triple beds but the price was good for us as budget travellers.
The buffet style breakfast served was nice. The staffs there can speak english that made everything goes smooth.
The location is good, within working distance to Metro and RER train. There are lot of restaurants and cafe nearby as well.

For sure the best hotel of his category I found in Paris! In this simple place, nothing is missing. It's a small hotel situated in an old building, but inside it was renovated and owners care of it. Many two start hotels in the town look so old and falling down, Lux hotel does not. My room (single) had a comfortable big bed in the corner and, even it wasn't too big, there was enough space for me and my stuff. It had a window facing the front street, a nice boulevard with trees in perfect Paris style. The bathroom was ok, the shower was working fine and warm water was always available withing few seconds. Both room and bathroom were clean. There's wifi in the rooms, the signal was strong and always working. The staff was there 24h, always nice and helpful. I also liked the area, it can be considered quiet for a town full of traffic like Paris. Next to the hotel there's a tea room and a couple of bakeries around, in case you don't take breakfast there. Lots of choice also for lunch and dinner, with many different restaurants and a fast food. There are two metro stop neat the hotel: Picpus is just 2 minutes away, Nation is something like 7-8 minutes from the hotel and it offer different lines, including RER. This stop was very useful for me. The price was interesting, considering the town is not the cheapest around. I will surely consider this hotel for my future trips in Paris, I was really satisfied.

The Good:

- The room was very clean.
- Great water pressure and the bathrooms are entirely renovated.
- Fantastic location. Extremely easy to get around.

The Bad:

- We stayed twice and had a problem with noise both times. I reserved here because reviews stated that the hotel was quiet. This was not the case. We could hear people talking very loudly outside past 12 AM and couldn't sleep. As well, we had noisy neighbors and could hear their every word until past 1 AM (yelling, laughing, etc). Maybe this is normal for Paris hotels but it was extremely hard to get used to. However, the metro noise did not bother us at all.
